BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hoosier RiverWatch Powell Preserve Survey
DTSTART:20260618T090000
DTEND:20260618T103000
UID:544b49145117e6a417017eef86efe889@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join Sycamore Land Trust and the Indiana Geological and Water 
 Survey to help monitor the health of local streams through Hoosier Riverwa
 tch at Powell Preserve. Volunteers will wade into the stream to collect an
 d identify aquatic macroinvertebrates and conduct chemical water quality t
 ests\, helping track seasonal changes in stream health at two protected pr
 operties along Beanblossom Creek. We’ll discuss how geology\, land use\,
  and forest cover influence water conditions. All monitoring supplies are 
 provided through a grant from IDEM\, and no prior experience is required. 
 Participants should be comfortable standing and walking in shallow water. 
 Join us to learn more about Hoosier Riverwatch and contribute valuable dat
 a that supports Indiana’s waterways. Powell Preserve is not open to the 
 public.
LOCATION:Powell Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/05/hoosier-riverwatch-powell-preser
 ve-survey/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hoosier RiverWatch Trevlac Bluffs Survey
DTSTART:20260617T090000
DTEND:20260617T103000
UID:ea0d9aa9c2435d17c146fa37ca0cf156@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join Sycamore Land Trust and the Indiana Geological and Water 
 Survey to help monitor the health of local streams through Hoosier Riverwa
 tch at Trevlac Bluffs Nature Preserve. Volunteers will wade into the strea
 m to collect and identify aquatic macroinvertebrates and conduct chemical 
 water quality tests\, helping track seasonal changes in stream health at t
 wo protected properties along Beanblossom Creek. We’ll discuss how geolo
 gy\, land use\, and forest cover influence water conditions. All monitorin
 g supplies are provided through a grant from IDEM\, and no prior experienc
 e is required. Participants should be comfortable standing and walking in 
 shallow water. Join us to learn more about Hoosier Riverwatch and contribu
 te valuable data that supports Indiana’s waterways.
LOCATION:Trevlac Bluffs Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/05/hoosier-riverwatch-trevlac-bluff
 s-survey/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hike the Trust: Eagle Slough Natural Area
DTSTART:20260614T090000
DTEND:20260614T110000
UID:2a6108262879592297f836c55366bb33@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Explore one of southern Indiana’s unique wetland ecosystems 
 at Eagle Slough Natural Area as part of our Hike the Trust series. A sloug
 h is a slow-moving wetland (a mix of backwater channels\, open water\, and
  bottomland forest) that supports diverse plants\, filters water\, and pro
 vides wildlife habitat. At Eagle Slough\, we’ll hike the trail and visit
  observation decks to see wetland plants\, listen for breeding birds\, and
  learn about this unusual swamp-forest ecosystem and the towering bald cyp
 ress trees that still thrive here. ***This hike will start at 9am Central 
 Time***
LOCATION:Eagle Slough Natural Area
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/05/hike-the-trust-eagle-slough-natu
 ral-area/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Prothonotary Warblers in the Wetlands with Cathy Meyer
DTSTART:20260613T073000
DTEND:20260613T093000
UID:ae9aeb630b33090852cfafaa4272070b@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Have you seen any swamp candles yet this year? Join expert bir
 der Cathy Meyer to spot the vibrant Prothonotary Warbler\, Indiana’s onl
 y nesting warbler that prefers flooded forests and swampy areas. Learn abo
 ut its fascinating nesting habits\, preferred habitats\, and the role it p
 lays in the wetland ecosystem\, while listening and looking for other resi
 dent and migratory birds. Perfect for both beginner and experienced birder
 s eager to connect with the sights and sounds of southern Indiana’s summ
 er wetlands.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/05/prothonotary-warblers-in-the-wet
 lands-with-cathy-meyer/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Little Hikers: Frog Calls
DTSTART:20260612T093000
DTEND:20260612T113000
UID:0f8e1555022b5925ceccf00363f2f168@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Hop into spring at Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve as we l
 isten for frogs across the preserve. As we walk the boardwalks and trails\
 , we’ll look and listen for familiar wetland voices like spring peepers\
 , chorus frogs\, American toads\, and northern leopard frogs\, learning wh
 y they call and how each species’ sound is unique. Little Hikers and the
 ir caregivers will discover how frogs use wetlands like Beanblossom Bottom
 s to survive and why these habitats are so important for amphibians and pe
 ople alike. All ages are welcome.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/05/little-hikers-frog-calls/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Preserve-a-Preserve: Weed Wrangle at Beanblossom Bottoms
DTSTART:20260529T100000
DTEND:20260529T120000
UID:fc1577f498a9fdef7e6bfd83e8c66a09@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Spend a day tromping through wetlands during our Beanblossom B
 ottoms Nature Preserve Weed Wrangle as we work together to remove invasive
  cattails. Over the past couple of years\, storms and tornado damage have 
 opened the canopy in parts of the preserve\, allowing more sunlight to rea
 ch the wetlands\, which causes aggressive species like cattails to spread.
  Participants will work off-trail in shallow water\, using cut-stump techn
 iques to target cattails to help restore native wetland vegetation. By red
 ucing cattail dominance\, we can improve habitat for birds\, amphibians\, 
 and aquatic invertebrates while supporting the wetland’s natural recover
 y after these landscape-altering events.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/04/preserve-a-preserve-weed-wrangle
 -at-beanblossom-bottoms-3/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
