BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Free virtual lecture: The Lives and Times of Midwest Amphibians wi
 th Dr. Spencer Cortwright
DTSTART:20260528T190000
DTEND:20260528T203000
UID:98da05f623066c829b7ce3119d223c81@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Each spring amphibians bring great joy as they seem to suddenl
 y emerge from a frozen landscape. Join us for a free virtual lecture and Q
 &amp\;A with Dr. Spencer Cortwright\, Professor of Biology at Indiana Univ
 ersity Northwest and longtime researcher of amphibian and restoration ecol
 ogy. Dr. Cortwright will take us on a richly illustrated journey through t
 he lives of Midwestern amphibians\, exploring their year-round life cycles
 \, seasonal movements\, and the remarkable adaptations that help them tran
 sition from a frozen landscape to springtime abundance.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/03/the-lives-and-times-of-midwest-a
 mphibians-with-dr-spencer-cortwright/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
