BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wildflower Meadow Preserve-a-Preserve Volunteer Weed Wrangle
DTSTART:20260804T080000
DTEND:20260804T110000
UID:26aa059513b1bcd2991dfdbd846cebad@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Volunteers are invited to help Sycamore Land Trust and Blazing
  Star CISMA conserve native biodiversity\, gain hands-on experience in lan
 d stewardship\, and help maintain natural areas at the Touch the Earth Nat
 ural Area in Bartholomew County! Weed Wrangle events are fun and education
 al opportunities to learn how to identify and control the invasive plants 
 that are negatively impacting our preserves and other green spaces in our 
 community. The focus for this volunteer event will be the identification a
 nd control of invasive plants and other non-desirable woody vegetation wit
 hin a wildflower meadow restoration in the new 10 acre addition to the pre
 serve.
LOCATION:Touch the Earth Natural Area
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2023/07/wildflower-meadow-preserve-a-pre
 serve-volunteer-weed-wrangle/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
